responding: Also avoid using joins that cause huge explosions of records, which counterintuitively even an inner join can do, if you have repeating join keys. Outer and cross join are a huge culprit. Do these in SQL and return results instead - perhaps in #SQLite or #MySQL.

content: If all fails, consider #parallelism. Pandas #serial processes data, but you can try #dask or #modin which both do parallelised operations. There are also packages such as #joblib which are useful for parallelism. It can handle #multiprocessing and #threading.
